<div class='page-info span-24'>
  <div class="span-22 append-1 prepend-1">
    <h2>About The Dataset</h2>
    <p>
    The data set comes <%= link_to "The Tornado History Project Website", "http://www.tornadohistoryproject.com/" %>.
    <br/>
    <br/>
    The data covers the years 1950-2010. After downloading everything, the data was fairly easy to work with since it came in a comma separate value format. There were a number
    of values that were not necessary so I ran them through a simple java program to parse them out. 
    <br/>
    <br/>
    The only other hiccup came when I noticed the data after 1997 looked slightly odd. As it turns out they have a notice on the website saying the format changed. So I had to 
    change the columns that had a different format to the correct format with a java program as well. Once that was commplete all the data was ready to be used.
    <br/>
    <br/>
    The final thing to acquire was a high resolution map of the United States that fit the latitude longitde coordinates of my data. Google was very helpful there.
    <br/>
    <br/>
    As I was creating this application, I though it would be very useful to see this in Google Earth. Each tornado would be represented as a colored pin. Then each pin would be clickable and 
    give specific details about each Tornado such as distance traveled in miles, total property damage, fujita value, injuries, fatalities, and width of the Tornado in Yards.
    </p>
